org.presentation.persistence.business

Interface PersistenceFacade

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PersistenceFacadeImpl

    public interface PersistenceFacade
    Interface which serves as middle business side between modules, which requires ability to query data from and to database, and the specific implementation of implementation of integration DAO classes.
    Author:
    radio.koza

    • Method Detail

      • createNewUser

        boolean createNewUser(String email,
                      String pass,
                      String name,
                      String surname)
        Method creates new user in database by using email, password, user's name and surname. Implementation should be cappable to work with salts and hashing if it is specified so in database model.
        Parameters:
        email - Email of the new user
        pass - Password of the new user given as plain text in utf-8 encoding
        name - First name of the new user
        surname - Surname of the new user
        Returns:
        true if user was created sucessfully; false otherwise

      • findUser

        User findUser(String email)
        Method finds user in database by user's email address (primary key). If there is no user with specified email, method returns null.
        Parameters:
        email - Email of the user to be seeked
        Returns:
        User with matching email or null if there is no user with such email address

      • editUser

        void editUser(User user)
        Method edits user matching the specified email address. Note that this method should not be used to update collection values inside User class but should use proper methods instead. Editing of collection is not necessary functionable because of JPA owning side problem.
        Parameters:
        user - Specific instance of User class defining the new state of user with same email address

      • addUserLogin

        void addUserLogin(User user,
                  String address)
        Method adds new Login object to the specified user passed as parameter. Login is created by using contemporary date and address (IP) passed in parameter.
        Parameters:
        user - User instance which new Login should be added to
        address - String representation of IP address from which is user logged in

      • findLastUserLogin

        Login findLastUserLogin(User user)
        Method finds Login instance of the specified user's last login. If there is no user with such email address or found user does have no logins, method returns null.
        Parameters:
        user - Instance of User that the Login should be found for
        Returns:
        Last Instance of Login representing last user login; null if user not found or user have no logins

      • findUserLogins

        List<Login> findUserLogins(User user)
        Method finds collection of all user logins (instance of Login) of the user specified as method parameter.
        Parameters:
        user - User that Login collection should be found for
        Returns:
        Collection of user logins; collection can be empty if user was not found in database or user does have no logins; never returns null

      • createNewCheckup

        void createNewCheckup(Checkup checkup)
        Method creates new checkup by using instance of Checkup class. Note that checkup passed as parameter must have set mandatory database field and also User instance set through method Checkup.setUser(org.presentation.persistence.model.User).
        Parameters:
        checkup - New checkup that should be persisted in database

      • updateCheckup

        void updateCheckup(Checkup checkup)
        Method updates checkup passed as parameter. Checkup is found by primary key specified in passed instance of Checkup and merged to database with new values. Note that this method should not be used for updating collection of Checkup.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Instance of Checkup to be merged into database with new values

      • findUserCheckings

        List<Checkup> findUserCheckings(User user)
        Method finds collection of Checkup class of specified User. Collection can be empty if no checkup was found but collection is never null.
        Parameters:
        user - User for which to find collection of checkups
        Returns:
        Collection of user's Checkup

      • findUserCheckings

        List<Checkup> findUserCheckings(User user,
                                int offset,
                                int count)
        Method finds collection of Checkup class of specified User. Method uses attibutes offset and count to limitate count and start position on database query level.
        Parameters:
        user - Instance of User to search checkups for
        offset - Index of first check-up to return (indexing from 0)
        count - Count of check-ups to return (could be fewer if specified count of results is not in database)
        Returns:
        Collection of Checkup as query result; this is never null but could be empty

      • listGraphTypes

        List<String> listGraphTypes(Checkup checkup)
        Returns list of names of graph types assigned to specified Checkup. Checkup have always at least one graph with specified graph type. There is possible to find Graph of specified type with specified Checkup by calling method findGraphByGraphType(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that graph types should be found for
        Returns:
        List of graph types represented by String of distinct graph types found in specific Checkup

        graphType - Graph type name applied as filter
        Returns:

      • findCheckupMessages

        List<Message> findCheckupMessages(Checkup checkup)
        Method finds collection of all Message assigned to specified Checkup.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be taken from
        Returns:
        List of Message objects assigned to specified Checkup

      • findCheckupMessages

        List<Message> findCheckupMessages(Checkup checkup,
                                  int offset,
                                  int count)
        Method does the same functionality as addMessagesToCheckup(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List, java.lang.String), but moreover the results are filtered by its position and limited in count. Eg. method with offset = 50 and count = 50 returns second fifty messages of the specified Checkup. Optimization of this method should be implemented in database layer and so this method should have effective querying of data.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        offset - Index of first message element (indexed from zero)
        count - Count of wanted messaged (method could return less than count when there are not enough message elements in database)
        Returns:
        List of Message with List.size() <= count

      • findCheckupMessageResources

        List<String> findCheckupMessageResources(Checkup checkup)
        Method lists all distinct names of message producers of specified Checkup. (eg. Web Crawler, ...). Resource name returned in list have at least on message logged in checkup.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        Returns:
        List of distinct message producer names that have at least one message logged in checkup

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResource

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResource(Checkup checkup,
                                              String resource)
        Method finds collection of Message objects assigned to specified Checkup and produced by message producer represented by resource name.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resource - Name of message producer resource represented by String
        Returns:
        List of Message matching specified filter

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResource

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResource(Checkup checkup,
                                              String resource,
                                              int offset,
                                              int count)
        Method has same functionality as findCheckupMessagesWithResource(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.lang.String) but moreover it is possible to filter results by indexing start location and final count. Functionality is implemented on database query level and so calling of this method is much more effective. This functionality is useful for paginator in presentation tier.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resource - Name of the message producer represented by String
        offset - Index of the first message indexed from zero
        count - Count of messages wanted to query
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching filter where List.size() <= count

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResources

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResources(Checkup checkup,
                                               List<String> resources)
        Method has same functionality as findCheckupMessagesWithResource(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.lang.String) but there can be used more message producer names to filter results.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resources - List of message producer names
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching the filter

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResources

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResources(Checkup checkup,
                                               List<String> resources,
                                               int offset,
                                               int count)
        Method has same functionality as findCheckupMessagesWithResources(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List) but moreover it is possible to filter results by indexing start location and final count. Functionality is implemented on database query level and so calling of this method is much more effective. This functionality is useful for paginator in presentation tier.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resources - List of message producer names
        offset - Index of the first message indexed from zero
        count - Count of messages wanted to query
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching filter where List.size() <= count

      • findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators(Checkup checkup,
                                                    List<String> discriminators)
        Method finds collection of Message object assigned to specified Checkup and filtered by message discriminators. Discriminator is fully qualified name of the Message implementation. (eg. org.presentation.model.logging.InfoMsg).
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        discriminators - List of discriminators passed as instance of String
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching filter

      • findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators(Checkup checkup,
                                                    List<String> discriminators,
                                                    int offset,
                                                    int count)
        Method has same functionality as findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List) but moreover it is possible to filter results by indexing start location and final count. Functionality is implemented on database query level and so calling of this method is much more effective. This functionality is useful for paginator purposes.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        discriminators - List of message discriminators passed as instance of String
        offset - Index of the first message indexed from zero
        count - Count of messages wanted to query
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching filter where List.size() <= count

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResourcesDiscriminators

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResourcesDiscriminators(Checkup checkup,
                                                             List<String> resources,
                                                             List<String> discriminators)
        Method merges together functionality of findCheckupMessagesWithDiscriminators(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List) and findCheckupMessagesWithResources(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List).
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resources - List of resource names represented by String
        discriminators - List of message discriminators represented by String
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching the filter

      • findCheckupMessagesWithResourcesDiscriminators

        List<Message> findCheckupMessagesWithResourcesDiscriminators(Checkup checkup,
                                                             List<String> resources,
                                                             List<String> discriminators,
                                                             int offset,
                                                             int count)
        Method has the same functionality as findCheckupMessagesWithResourcesDiscriminators(org.presentation.persistence.model.Checkup, java.util.List, java.util.List) but moreover it is possible to filter results by indexing start location and final count. Functionality is implemented on database query level and so calling of this method is much more effective. This functionality is useful for paginator purposes.
        Parameters:
        checkup - Checkup that messages should be found for
        resources - List of resource names represented by String
        discriminators - List of message discriminators represented by String
        offset - Index of the first message indexed from zero
        count - Count of messages wanted to query
        Returns:
        List of Message objects matching the filter where List.size() <= count

      • flush

        void flush()
        Method flushes persistence context to database. This is useful when it is necessary to assign primary keys to newly created entity classes and then use the primary keys in the single transaction.
